1.2 Management System

ACT has developed a management system to implement and maintain compliance with the Risk Management Program.  This management system identifies lines of responsibility for the entire program and each of its key elements.  The Plant Manager has primary responsibility for developing and implementing the RMP.  The Plant Manager and the Electrical Engineer alternate on-call responsibilities (2 weeks on, 2 weeks off), with the Logistics Manager providing backup for these individuals if they are out of town.  The Shift Leader on duty is the primary Emergency Coordinator in the event of any spill or release, with immediate notification of the above-listed on-call personnel required.  Plant Operators are required to inspect storage and operating areas at least once per shift.  In addition, Operators log the material levels in each bulk storage tank twice per shift.

